"Name: {name}, Score: {score}".format(**info)
Q28. Check numeric integer string (not float)?
A:

"12345".isdigit()    # True
"12.5".isdigit()     # False
For negatives/signs, isdigit() is False ("-5"). Use careful parsing/int() with try/except when needed.

Q29. Character frequency?
A:

from collections import Counter
Counter("banana")   # {'a':3,'n':2,'b':1}
Or: {ch: s.count(ch) for ch in set(s)} (slower for large strings).

Q30. Remove all vowels (case-insensitive)?
A:

import re
re.sub(r'(?i)[aeiou]', '', "Hello World")  # 'Hll Wrld'
Or comprehension:

''.join(ch for ch in s if ch.lower() not in 'aeiou')
Q31. split() vs split(' ')?
A:

split() — splits on any whitespace, removes empty chunks
split(' ') — splits only on single space; can keep empties
"a  b".split()      # ['a','b']
"a  b".split(' ')   # ['a', '', 'b']
Q32. partition / rpartition?
A: Splits into 3 parts at first/last separator:

"sai@gmail.com".partition("@")
# ('sai', '@', 'gmail.com')
Useful for email-like parsing.

