Q44. f-string expression power?
A:

print(f"{name.upper():*^12}")
print(f"{3.14159:.2f}")
Supports expressions, format specs.

Q45. % formatting vs format vs f-string?
A:

% — older
str.format — flexible, reusable templates
f-strings — fastest/readable for most inline cases
Q46. Casefold vs lower for comparisons?
A: casefold() is stronger for caseless matching (Unicode), e.g. German ß → ss. Prefer for international case-insensitive compare.

a.casefold() == b.casefold()
Q47. Remove prefix/suffix (3.9+)?
A:

"Test.py".removesuffix(".py")
"pre_value".removeprefix("pre_")
Q48. Memory note: slices?
A: Slicing creates a new string (copy of selected chars). Large repeated slices can cost memory/time.

Q49. Build anagram check interview answer?
A:

from collections import Counter
def anagram(a, b):
    return Counter(a.replace(" ", "").lower()) == Counter(b.replace(" ", "").lower())
Q50. First non-repeating character?
A:

from collections import Counter
def first_unique(s):
    c = Counter(s)
    for ch in s:
        if c[ch] == 1:
            return ch
    return None
Q51. Validate email simply vs robustly?
A: Simple: one @, split user/domain, domain whitelist (your mini-project).
Robust: regex/email-validator libraries; still not perfect without sending confirmation.

