Q53. in operator on strings?
A: Checks substring membership:

"py" in "python"   # True
"" in "python"     # True (empty string is substring)
Q54. Design: normalize user input names?
A:

name = input().strip()
name = " ".join(name.split())   # collapse inner spaces
name = name.title()
Q55. 30-second interview summary.
A: Strings are immutable Unicode sequences. Manipulate via indexing/slicing and methods (upper, strip, find, replace, split/join, validation, formatting). Prefer join for building, f-strings for formatting, translate/regex for advanced cleaning, and always remember methods return new strings.

